About Us
We all have our improvement stories to tell. At LIC we believe in constant improvement, never settling and always striving for greatness. We know little improvements can add up to huge gains for our customers, and for our country. We value NZ primary industries and will do whatever it takes to support and grow our farmer community. We're down to earth and we're a diverse bunch - a mix of super smart scientists, veterinarians, farmers, sales people and clever marketing folk. We are inclusive and count ourselves lucky to have people from all backgrounds working with us.
LIC is based in Newstead, Hamilton, where we enjoy more affordable housing, relaxed commuting, easy parking and a readily accessible outdoor lifestyle. Our campus is in a rural setting just outside Hamilton and includes a social club, swimming pool, onsite parking, tennis and volleyball courts and a café with great coffee. We also offer generous sick leave entitlements, extra leave days per year, family leave for new parents, discounted insurance, employee shares scheme, mental health & well-being program, internal training programmes and an employee assistance programme to name but a few - and we're still working on improvements!

About the Role
Our commercial team is the hub of new growth for our organisation, including opportunity identification, validation, implementation, project management, growing new businesses as well as acquiring new business.
In this role you will be responsible for evaluating growth opportunities and identifying opportunities to fill the Commercial Pipeline. You will drive Commercial strategic alignment activities and add value to Commercial through assessing and progressing new opportunities. Some of your key focus will include:
Develop and lead the identification and evaluation of agri-techology start-up opportunities;
Research, analyse, interpret and present data to aid and enable the strategic decision making surrounding new commercial opportunities.
Assist the Corporate Development Manager in the management of the LIC Commercial Pipeline, including overseeing the balance and prioritisation of commercial opportunities;
Understand LIC's long-term strategies to support, facilitate and enable the identification and/or evaluation of opportunities for growth to help LIC achieve its business goals;
Support the concept development of strategic opportunities for the Commercial Group including identifying, evaluating, scoping, critically analysing and presenting information on industry trends, stakeholder needs and new innovations.

About You
We are seeking a quality focused individual with exceptional integrity and business acumen. To be successful you will need to demonstrate the following:
Demonstrated experience in a business environment, preferably in strategy development roles;
Able to deal with ambiguity and being at the forefront of strategy;
Strength in problem solving, critical thinking, analytical thinking, conceptual design and facilitation;
Experience in building and developing strategic concepts;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Deep understanding of business alliance issues and practice;
Strong experience in building relationships and rapport with key stakeholders;
An acute sense of integrity is required as the jobholder will be privy to confidential and commercially sensitive information.
To be successful at LIC means you'll thrive in a fast-paced, busy environment and you'll be adaptable to change. You'll also enjoy working within a team of dedicated individuals, and be able to deliver a professional approach when working with a wide array of customers.

How to Apply
If you're after a rewarding and social career with people who embrace our company values of Integrity, Innovation, Spirit of Co-Operation, In-tune and Passion, then we would consider ourselves lucky to welcome you on-board.
For more information and to apply, go to our website www.careers.lic.co.nz/open-positions
